<subSubSection id="AD0A748E44F4507FC7C4507C5F8BAA7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="73A9F78D353EF8FC4C22E15D1A73BBAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D33146FD99BA1B6BD0B1CB7B747FBB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">The name refers to the velvety colony morphology of this fungus on MEA.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AC2A6B77E460A1AD4ABD58B4561DDDB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D4E050770BBFF2C5D8B7D3EEFA817CE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6BBF7D50762FB1DE73396395B87365E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">
<taxonomicName id="F0A0072948A7C6315F81265ACB448AF2" authorityName="R. L. Chang &amp; X. Y. Zhang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiostomataceae" genus="Sporothrix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sporothrix villosa" order="Ophiostomatales" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="D2B2924E6357EB863978CE4C8EC8A243" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Sporothrix villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="40A8A5C17DB2083D83AE5EF87895912B" genus="S." lsidName="S. abietina" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" rank="species" species="abietina">
<emphasis id="11AC536441BF8EC00E6118A537012360" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">S. abietina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the production of smaller conidia and slow growth rate on MEA at 35 °C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="679CBFDDF022F88B3BC6C4A1011BF00A" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="973426AF4A0FCF6EB6136967BD87078E" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E22BB69799C9ED4DB31A49DEB5C43F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">
Sexual morph is unknown. Asexual state sporothrix-like: the conidiophores directly arising from the vegetative hyphae, measuring (3.2-) 6.8-23.8 (-53.6) 
<normalizedToken id="086C469E21131DB0FA49DC4B09BEC220" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="2664E191C55C2DCF7049F6298469B8FD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(0.5-) 0.8-1.3 (-1.5) 
<normalizedToken id="99D9B02F1F0C96ADBF52F415CB13B020" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5F6E664DC964CF01CAFCD2F3C81243A" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Morphological characters of asexual structures of Sporothrix villosa sp. nov. a fourteen-day-old culture on MEA b-e conidiophores and conidia. - Scale bars: 10 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.83.70925.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/598900" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">13b, d and e</figureCitation>
); conidia hyaline, smooth, unicellular oblong to ovoid, with rounded ends, measuring (1.2-) 1.8-2.6 (-4.1) 
<normalizedToken id="C5E0AC620CAE30F294538D5AC0B815F3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(0.7-) 0.8-1.1 (-1.4) 
<normalizedToken id="0C6962D777168D1441B3B179956E47B5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A02EC162B33450847CC6760411A05299" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Morphological characters of asexual structures of Sporothrix villosa sp. nov. a fourteen-day-old culture on MEA b-e conidiophores and conidia. - Scale bars: 10 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.83.70925.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/598900" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">13c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="AB694568D8B478C7E4F6B66043D6842D" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.83.70925.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/598900" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" start="Figure 13" startId="F13">
<paragraph id="036CABE9555E47023BECF0DA6796221F" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="8AFCD9CC6503914B11BEB83B30E16970" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Figure 13.</emphasis>
Morphological characters of asexual structures of 
<taxonomicName id="33BD35AF44B506A6F01B10295ED8C5FE" authorityName="R. L. Chang &amp; X. Y. Zhang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiostomataceae" genus="Sporothrix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sporothrix villosa" order="Ophiostomatales" pageId="0" pageNumber="181" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="1BAF02D6D36FC62C39FFEAFB9A314DED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">Sporothrix villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="24AF71DDACF45B4CB0315B34935C56E4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">a</emphasis>
fourteen-day-old culture on MEA 
<emphasis id="5909EEBFDD064D57CAA18E3B9A55B891" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="181">b-e</emphasis>
